<br>
Pet classes cried about not being able to solo effectively... so SOE said fine, if YOU do ANY damage to a mob, you'll get ALL the exp, not you and your pet.<br>
<br>
Now..<br>
<br>
Enchanters are complaining that they can't have a hasted pet?  Sorry, mage pets CANT kill mobs by themselves, nor necro pets, nor ::laugh:: SK pets, Shaman pets, Cleric ::takes a stroke:: pet, druid pets (charmed), ranger pets (do they get charm?), Beastlord pets... <br>
<br>
NO PETS except for Enchanter pets... can kill mobs without outside help (ok, MAYBE a shaman).  The reason?.. even though Shaman have the best slow in the game, the Enchanter gets the best haste.  Close.. but far enough apart to be a big difference.<br>
<br>
And what about your group members?  the INSTANCE that hasted-charmed pet breaks charm, your chanter is gonna scream bloddy murder!! Leaving the cleric to try and heal, thus getting agro either after successfully saving the chanter, or AFTER the chanter dies..<br>
<br>
Bottom line.. so what?  You'll just have to use a little more mana while you solo (C5 anyone?).  I have no sympathy for any class that has the ability to SOLO lvl 65 mobs, when it comes to nerfing THAT ability.<br>
<br>
**note**(solo = using ALL of your classes abilities to kill said mob without help from another PC)<br>
<br>
Channeling is a WONDERFUL skill.... but not THAT wonderful. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=198804">Venerable Impudent Blasphemy</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
