<br>
No, it does not.  The 1% slow <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>so far</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has only been added to new PoP charms.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> With the 1% slow added to the charm, do mobs that cast slow spells break the pet's charm, or are the pets immune to the slow? Seems like it would have to be one or the other, since slows don't stack. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually bard slows and enchanter/shaman slows stack just fine and have been since before ... whatever. Note that only the highest slow factor takes effect. Bard slow songs have their slow component in slot 1. Enchanter/shaman slows all have their slow component in slot 2. The new charm slow components are all in slot 7, so they will stack with all the other slows in game.<br>
<br>
