<br>
We heal and buff your pet, keep stuff snared...you slow your target down, yadda yadda its all good. <br>
<br>
Hell, done it already with the chanters in HoH before and I didn't even watch the exp...was just fun having a temp tank walk around and keeping it alive while it pounded on other ones.<br>
<br>
I sympathize with Enchanters who solo mostly because I know the freedom of it. I admit I'm jealous of the amount of AA they can make from it, but I can symphathize. Why join a pickup group and risk sitting there doing the same ol' boring shit day after day, when you can solo and have a little fun. Dying in the Planes doesn't mean much anymore thanks to the GY, so just loot your corpse except for a bum item, and go back to play for now. People bug me for soloing so much, but lemme see....do what I want, kill what I want, and how I want to do it....OR...sit there and have to be the healer I really don't want to be. <br>
<br>
Part of the thrill of soloing is just knowing what your class can do. Enchanters shouldn't have to be bound to groups any more than most other classes shouldn't be (unfortunately some are <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), and there should be at least a fair way to solo or group.<br>
<br>
But in all seriousness like I posted before, it'll just weed out who IS and who IS NOT. Most of the chanters I've shared the soloing fields with are pretty good, but then there's always a rare one who's just milking it because its easy. As in any class, the ones who want to prevail will find a way...the ones who want to pout about it, will have groups for audiences to hear their whining.<br>
<br>
As for enchanter-group work...<br>
<br>
They gave most classes new ways to regen mana. Only reason anyone uses the excuse for c3+ is so they can have an easier means to do what they're supposed to be doing already. Or does everyone and their uncle NOT have a horse by now somehow?  <br>
<br>
Druids and Rangers both have snares to pull away adds, and NOW they have damageless roots (Earthen Roots). This can make them decent ghetto-mezzers.<br>
<br>
Most other casters have damageless root too...won't elaborate too much, mages don't have it i think though (so don't kill for me not knowing this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
Druids, Rangers, and Clerics have a form of &quot;harmony&quot;. If that isn't easy enough for single-pulling, FD pulling is an old tool...if you're one of those classes that can and haven't done it before by the time you're post-60, well....I really don't know. I'd feel sorry for you if I didn't wonder how the hell you haven't yet.<br>
<br>
Shamans can slow, and other classes (like Beastlords and Epic'd rangers) can too. Yeah the non-shamans aren't exactly gauranteed or the best, but its some form of it anyway.<br>
<br>
<br>
You have to admit, you don't always need an enchanter, it just makes experiencing a lot more easier. Unfortunately chanters have a new tool to play with and aren't just stuck to groups anymore, so what's the real issue? <br>
<br>
Jealous of the experience they're getting?<br>
<br>
Or the fact that they now have the freedom you don't?<br>
